#!/usr/bin/perl -w

use xPL::Dock qw/-run/;

=head1 NAME

xpl-heyu - Perl script for an xPL X10 application

=head1 SYNOPSIS

  xpl-heyu [flags] [options]
  where valid flags are:
    --help         - show this help text
    --verbose      - verbose mode (for the xPL layer)
    --heyu-verbose - verbose mode (for the heyu layer)
  and valid options are (default shown in brackets):
    --interface if0            - the interface for xPL messages (first
                                 non-loopback or loopback)

  # start the x10 application on first ethernet interface in verbose mode
  xpl-heyu --interface eth0 --verbose --heyu-verbose

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This script is an xPL client that interfaces with an X10 controller using
the 'heyu' tools.

=head1 SEE ALSO

xPL::Dock::Heyu(3), xPL::Dock(3), heyu(1)

Project website: http://www.xpl-perl.org.uk/

